    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 2000, 4000, 8000 - LIGHT SYSTEMS - DESCRIPTION - Fog Light
        System
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Fog Light System</title>
        <para>Fog lights are rectangular halogen lights mounted in the bumper opening and are available with either
            amber or clear lenses. These lights are wired so that they are not illuminated when the headlights are on
            Hi-Beam. They will only operate with the headlight switch on and the dimmer switch in the Low-Beam position.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
